Audio failure between Windows Messenger App <-> Portal Mini

Not sure how to rageshake portal so post it here
My husband called me through Windows Desktop Messenger App to Portal mini around 5pm today, it connected but I could only hear a weird loud beeping sound; I called back to him, connected successfully, but I cannot hear anything again. We had to switch to other ways to communicate with each other (we are practicing social distancing under the same roof, I would rule out networking problem).

      Accessibility
      Accessibility
      Documentation
      Accessibility Group
      Empathy Lab
      To get started, click on 'show all headings' or 'unlabelled form elements' in the nub. To test your feature alone, click the 'Test your Feature' button and click on your feature to run the tests.
      Test your Feature
      Take the HIKE below to test for accessibility!
      H Headings and semantics
      Write semantic markup so screen readers can understand them i.e. use tags such as h2, ul, button instead of unsemantic divs.
      Show all headings
      Show all landmark roles
      I Images and non-text content
      Images and other non-text content need textual descriptions so screen readers can announce them correctly i.e images need an alt text (alt="" if decorative), image only buttons need labels and videos need captions.
      Images without alt attributes
      Links with images that have alt=""
      K Keyboard navigation
      Keyboard only and screen reader users cannot use the mouse. So, make your content usable with just the keyboard and manage keyboard focus.
      Links without href attributes
      Buttons built with unsemantic divs or spans
      E Extra love: ARIA
      ARIA attributes such as aria-label, role, aria-checked convey additional info to screen readers.
      Links with href="#" and no role attribute
      Unlabeled form elements
      Show all roles
      Show basic ARIA attributes
      Internationalization (aka i18n)
      Almost TWO BILLION people on Facebook have already selected a language other than English.
      Help them have the most complete experience possible by applying internationalization concepts and features right from the start for their language, units, currencies and more. Here is sample of resources available:
      For everyone:
      i18n Help Center | Q&A group | FYI group
      For engineers:
      Dex info for FBT, Android, iOS, RTL, and more!
      For designers:
      Help Center Topics  | Sketch plugin
      For QA:
      i18n QA process
      Also see:
      Request translation | Report issues with translations
      Check our new Points of contact on i18n/l10n/Local Insights dashboard for information on locales and their overall level of internal support, contact information for those locales, as well as points of contact for the various vertical and products amongst i18n and l10n teams.
      Use the menu below to switch to a different language, including test versions like fb_HA (FB Hash), fake Chinese or fake RTL. Give it a try!
